    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-10T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="1000"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1000">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.05/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Southard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-10T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 10, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. Reference your despatch No. 179, April 10.<note n="4" xml:id="d1000fn4">Not
                        printed.</note> While establishment in Ethiopia of a court having
                    jurisdiction over foreign nationals would, in principle, be agreeable to the
                    Department, it believes the proposal of the Diplomatic Corps at Addis Ababa
                    needs further redrafting and consideration.</p>
                <p>Prior to preparing definite instructions, the Department would like to be
                    informed of the attitude of the other powers interested. You should discreetly
                    endeavor to ascertain this from your colleagues.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
